//+++++++++++++++++++++++
// DaedRamses\'s ENB v3.0
//+++++++++++++++++++++++
If you decided to download this Enb you will have to follow some steps to make it work.
first I would suggest downloading some enviroment tweakes like \"Realistic Water\" or \"2K Textures\".
I hope you will enjoy this ENB!!

//+++++++++++++++++++++++
// Requirements
//+++++++++++++++++++++++
1)You will have to download a ENB Series d3d9.dll file from one of these: |[URL=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0102.htm]v0.102[/URL]| |[URL=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0103.htm]v0.103[/URL]| |[URL=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0112.htm]v0.112[/URL]| |[URL=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0113.htm]v0.113[/URL]|
The one that is most recommended is V0.113 there is almost no performance lost with it                                                             
download and paste it into your Skyrim directory

2)Your computer must be strong enough to handle this kind of graphic enhancment.

//+++++++++++++++++++++++
// Installation
//+++++++++++++++++++++++
1)Place all of the files from the \"ENB Settings by DaedRamses\" folder to your Skyrim Directory.

2)Place the file that is in the \"SkyrimPrefs ini\" folder to \"My Documents\\My Games\\Skyrim\".

3)Make sure that in the \"SkyrimPrefs.ini\" the \"bEnableFileSelection\" is set to 1 or else your ENB wont work.

//+++++++++++++++++++++++
// How to use
//+++++++++++++++++++++++
1)In-game if you dont see any change in graphic, press \"Shift\" + \"F12\" to enable the ENB.

2)if you want SSAO enabled, in the \"enbseries.ini\" change \"EnableAmbientOcclusion=false\" to \"EnableAmbientOcclusion=true\".

3)if you want Depth of Field disabled, in the \"enbseries.ini\" change \"EnableDepthOfField=true\" to \"EnableDepthOfField=false\".

